The only input line contains an integer n, the number of rows and columns of the matrix grid. The next n lines contain n integers each, representing the rows of the matrix grid.



Output

Output a single integer that represents the size of the array returned by the method. Output 0 if there is no good subset. Then, output the elements of the array returned by the method in the same line, separated by spaces.



Constraints

1 <= n <= 100
0 <= grid[i][j] <= 1



Example

Input:

